children.text: There have not been anti-skid blocks installed under the valley trusses in all areas, which may allow the trusses to slide down the roof over time if not installed.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 4440 – Installation of nail-plaited timber roof trusses, clause 5.4.1 Valley truss connection, states that
‘Connection of valley trusses to the supporting truss shall be in accordance with the details shown and described in Figure 5.6’
Additional anti-skid blocks or brackets must be immediately installed to this roof.
